{
  "slug": "legacy-structure-and-repurposing",
  "type": "html",
  "title": "Path-Dependence in Systems",
  "concept": "A system carries forward structures built under past constraints even when those constraints disappear, as long as the inherited structure still functions adequately in the new regime.",
  "interactiveId": "fa611548-f534-4f49-b18f-c4dc83c7452f",
  "sourcePieceId": "f4c864dd-c622-421f-844d-2c8b39ea4430",
  "publishedAt": 1778442638329,
  "voiceScore": 90,
  "content": {
    "type": "html",
    "html": "<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n<meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n<title>Path-Dependence in Systems</title>\n<style>\n  :root {\n    --bg: #faf7f1;\n    --fg: #1a1a1a;\n    --muted: #6b6b6b;\n    --line: #e5e0d6;\n    --primary: #1a6b62;\n    --secondary: #c9a227;\n    --trace: #e8dcc0;\n  }\n  * { box-sizing: border-box; }\n  body {\n    font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, \"Segoe UI\", sans-serif;\n    margin: 0;\n    padding: 20px;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    background: var(--bg);\n    line-height: 1.5;\n  }\n  h2 {\n    font-size: 1.05rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    margin: 0 0 4px;\n  }\n  p.subhead {\n    margin: 0 0 20px;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .control-group {\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 18px;\n    margin-bottom: 24px;\n  }\n  .control {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 14px;\n  }\n  .control label {\n    font-weight: 500;\n    flex-shrink: 0;\n    min-width: 130px;\n  }\n  .control select {\n    flex: 1;\n    padding: 6px 10px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n    color: var(--fg);\n    cursor: pointer;\n  }\n  .control input[type=range] {\n    flex: 1;\n    accent-color: var(--primary);\n    min-width: 120px;\n  }\n  .control output {\n    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    min-width: 5ch;\n    text-align: right;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .stage {\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    padding: 24px;\n    margin: 24px 0;\n    min-height: 240px;\n    display: flex;\n    flex-direction: column;\n    gap: 20px;\n  }\n  .condition-bar {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    gap: 12px;\n    padding: 10px 14px;\n    background: var(--trace);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    font-size: 0.85rem;\n  }\n  .condition-bar strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  .system-visual {\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    gap: 16px;\n    padding: 20px;\n    background: var(--bg);\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    min-height: 100px;\n  }\n  .component {\n    width: 60px;\n    height: 60px;\n    border-radius: 4px;\n    position: relative;\n    transition: all 250ms ease-out;\n    display: flex;\n    align-items: center;\n    justify-content: center;\n    font-size: 0.75rem;\n    font-weight: 600;\n    color: #fff;\n    text-align: center;\n  }\n  .component.config-a {\n    background: var(--primary);\n  }\n  .component.config-b {\n    background: var(--secondary);\n  }\n  .component::after {\n    content: '';\n    position: absolute;\n    top: -6px;\n    right: -6px;\n    width: 12px;\n    height: 12px;\n    border-radius: 50%;\n    opacity: 0;\n    transition: opacity 250ms ease-out;\n  }\n  .component.match::after {\n    background: var(--primary);\n    opacity: 1;\n  }\n  .component.adequate::after {\n    background: var(--secondary);\n    opacity: 1;\n  }\n  .reading {\n    margin: 18px 0 6px;\n    padding: 10px 14px;\n    background: #fff;\n    border: 1px solid var(--line);\n    border-radius: 6px;\n    font-size: 0.9rem;\n  }\n  .reading strong {\n    font-weight: 600;\n  }\n  p.caption {\n    margin: 14px 0 0;\n    color: var(--muted);\n    font-size: 0.875rem;\n  }\n  @media (max-width: 480px) {\n    .control label {\n      min-width: 110px;\n    }\n    .system-visual {\n      flex-wrap: wrap;\n      gap: 12px;\n    }\n    .component {\n      width: 50px;\n      height: 50px;\n      font-size: 0.7rem;\n    }\n  }\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n<h2>Set the inherited structure, then change the operating conditions</h2>\n<p class=\"subhead\">The system carries forward what it was built with—it doesn't rebuild from scratch when conditions shift.</p>\n\n<div class=\"control-group\">\n  <div class=\"control\">\n    <label for=\"config\">Inherited structure:</label>\n    <select id=\"config\" aria-describedby=\"config-desc\">\n      <option value=\"a\">Config A (built under Regime 1)</option>\n      <option value=\"b\">Config B (built under Regime 2)</option>\n    </select>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"control\">\n    <label for=\"regime\">Operating regime:</label>\n    <input id=\"regime\" type=\"range\" min=\"0\" max=\"100\" value=\"0\" aria-describedby=\"regime-out\">\n    <output id=\"regime-out\" for=\"regime\">Regime 1</output>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"stage\">\n  <div class=\"condition-bar\">\n    <span>Conditions favor: <strong id=\"favor-label\">Config A</strong></span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"system-visual\">\n    <div class=\"component config-a\" id=\"comp1\">Part 1</div>\n    <div class=\"component config-a\" id=\"comp2\">Part 2</div>\n    <div class=\"component config-a\" id=\"comp3\">Part 3</div>\n  </div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"reading\">\n  Structure: <strong id=\"structure\">Config A</strong>.<br>\n  Performance: <strong id=\"performance\">Optimal match</strong>.<br>\n  System response: <strong id=\"response\">Persists unchanged</strong>.\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"caption\" id=\"caption\">Config A was built under Regime 1 conditions. The structure and the regime align—optimal performance. The system has no pressure to change.</p>\n\n<script>\n  (function () {\n    var configSelect = document.getElementById('config');\n    var regimeSlider = document.getElementById('regime');\n    var regimeOut = document.getElementById('regime-out');\n    var favorLabel = document.getElementById('favor-label');\n    var structure = document.getElementById('structure');\n    var performance = document.getElementById('performance');\n    var response = document.getElementById('response');\n    var caption = document.getElementById('caption');\n    var components = [\n      document.getElementById('comp1'),\n      document.getElementById('comp2'),\n      document.getElementById('comp3')\n    ];\n\n    function update() {\n      var config = configSelect.value;\n      var regime = +regimeSlider.value;\n\n      // Regime label\n      if (regime < 30) {\n        regimeOut.textContent = 'Regime 1';\n        favorLabel.textContent = 'Config A';\n      } else if (regime < 70) {\n        regimeOut.textContent = 'Mixed';\n        favorLabel.textContent = 'Neither strongly';\n      } else {\n        regimeOut.textContent = 'Regime 2';\n        favorLabel.textContent = 'Config B';\n      }\n\n      // Update visual to reflect inherited config\n      for (var i = 0; i < components.length; i++) {\n        components[i].className = 'component config-' + config;\n      }\n\n      // Structure label\n      structure.textContent = config === 'a' ? 'Config A' : 'Config B';\n\n      // Performance assessment (does the structure match the regime?)\n      var isMatch = false;\n      var isAdequate = false;\n      if (config === 'a' && regime < 30) {\n        isMatch = true;\n        performance.textContent = 'Optimal match';\n      } else if (config === 'b' && regime >= 70) {\n        isMatch = true;\n        performance.textContent = 'Optimal match';\n      } else if (config === 'a' && regime >= 30 && regime < 70) {\n        isAdequate = true;\n        performance.textContent = 'Adequate function';\n      } else if (config === 'b' && regime >= 30 && regime < 70) {\n        isAdequate = true;\n        performance.textContent = 'Adequate function';\n      } else if (config === 'a' && regime >= 70) {\n        isAdequate = true;\n        performance.textContent = 'Suboptimal but functional';\n      } else if (config === 'b' && regime < 30) {\n        isAdequate = true;\n        performance.textContent = 'Suboptimal but functional';\n      }\n\n      // Visual indicators (dot in corner)\n      for (var j = 0; j < components.length; j++) {\n        components[j].classList.remove('match', 'adequate');\n        if (isMatch) {\n          components[j].classList.add('match');\n        } else if (isAdequate) {\n          components[j].classList.add('adequate');\n        }\n      }\n\n      // Response (what happens to the system?)\n      if (isMatch) {\n        response.textContent = 'Persists unchanged';\n      } else if (isAdequate) {\n        response.textContent = 'Persists—functions well enough';\n      } else {\n        response.textContent = 'Persists—no mechanism to rebuild';\n      }\n\n      // Caption\n      if (config === 'a' && regime < 30) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Config A was built under Regime 1 conditions. The structure and the regime align—optimal performance. The system has no pressure to change.';\n      } else if (config === 'a' && regime >= 30 && regime < 70) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Config A in mixed conditions. Not optimal, but still functional. The inherited structure persists because it works well enough—rebuilding is costly and unnecessary.';\n      } else if (config === 'a' && regime >= 70) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Config A under Regime 2 conditions. Suboptimal—Regime 2 favors Config B. But Config A still functions. The system carries forward what it inherited, not what the current regime would build from scratch. This is path-dependence.';\n      } else if (config === 'b' && regime >= 70) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Config B was built under Regime 2 conditions. The structure and the regime align—optimal performance. The system has no pressure to change.';\n      } else if (config === 'b' && regime >= 30 && regime < 70) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Config B in mixed conditions. Not optimal, but still functional. The inherited structure persists because it works well enough—rebuilding is costly and unnecessary.';\n      } else if (config === 'b' && regime < 30) {\n        caption.textContent = 'Config B under Regime 1 conditions. Suboptimal—Regime 1 favors Config A. But Config B still functions. The system carries forward what it inherited, not what the current regime would build from scratch. This is path-dependence.';\n      }\n    }\n\n    configSelect.addEventListener('change', update);\n    regimeSlider.addEventListener('input', update);\n    update();\n  })();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  }
}
